  <reg:acttitle>Hydro and Power Authority Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Hydro and Power Authority Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e319" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definition</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation, <in:term>Act</in:term> means the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96212_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Hydro and Power Authority Act</in:doc></bcl:link>.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e012">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Purposes of authority</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e117">
        <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For the purposes of section 12 (1.1) (c) <in:desc>[other purposes of authority]</in:desc> of the Act, to promote the use of electricity is prescribed as a purpose of the authority.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
      <bcl:subsection id="d2e511">
        <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>For certainty, the purpose set out under subsection (1) includes promotion for the purpose of reducing greenhouse gas emissions.</bcl:text>
      </bcl:subsection>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96212_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Hydro and Power Authority Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 212, s. 38.]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
